index_terms: CHICAGO MILWAUKEE ST PAUL PACIFIC RAILROAD
summary: An ordinance relating to the franchise of the Chicago, Milwaukee and St. Paul Railway Company of Washington granted by Ordinance No. 17330, as amended by Ordinances Nos. 52459 and 67096, extending the term thereof to December 31, 1966, subject to termination by the City after December 31, 1956, amending Sections 1, 3, and 17 of said Ordinance No. 17330, as amended, and providing for an acceptance.
